<item>
            <title>[LU-11636] t-f test_mkdir() does not support interop with non DNEII servers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11636</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;test_mkdir() always creates striped dir, this breaks interop testing with non DNEII servers&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
test_mkdir() {
local stripe_count=2
$LFS mkdir -i$mdt_index -c$stripe_count $path 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;introduced by&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
commit c75aa6c74cd86c69de893395735a6725571f11f4
Author:     Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;andreas.dilger@intel.com&amp;gt;
AuthorDate: Mon Mar 20 23:45:28 2017 -0400
Commit:     Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;oleg.drokin@intel.com&amp;gt;
CommitDate: Thu Sep 21 06:13:00 2017 +0000
 
    LU-3308 tests: fix sanity/sanityn test_mkdir() usage
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
